<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="10.[227,1436,1652,1866]" box="[227,348,1652,1678]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<heading bold="true" box="[227,348,1652,1678]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" reason="6">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[227,348,1652,1678]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[227,1436,1652,1866]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">The genus can be recognized by the following characters: medium to large-sized; vertex slightly wider than long, with weak median carina; frons with a row of submarginal tubercules on each side, median carina short, sublateral carina indistinct; tegmen without hypocostal plate, Sc just reaching midlength of tegmen, MP forked near distal one-third of tegmen; hind wing trilobed; phallobase with dorsolateral lobe bearing a pair of strong processes apically; aedeagus with a pair of long hooks at middle.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
